label.value: external side of fungal-type cell wall

definition.value: The side of the fungal-type cell wall that is opposite to the side that faces the cell and its contents.
A transcription factor complex that is involved in regulating transcription from RNA polymerase III (Pol III) promoters. TFIIIE contains a specific subset of ribosomal proteins.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate, a derivative of phosphatidylinositol in which the inositol ring is phosphorylated at the 4' position.

A protein complex that is required for efficient splicing, and prevents leakage of unspliced pre-mRNAs from the nucleus (named for pre-mRNA REtention and Splicing). In Saccharomyces, the complex consists of Ist3p, Bud13p, and Pml1p.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any of the vitamin B6 compounds -  pyridoxal, pyridoxamine and pyridoxine and the active form, pyridoxal phosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with pyridoxal, 3-hydroxy-5-(hydroxymethyl)-2-methylpyridine-4-carbaldehyde, a form of vitamin B6.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with pyridoxamine, 4-(aminomethyl)-5-(hydroxymethyl)-2-methylpyridin-3-ol, a form of vitamin B6.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with pyridoxine, 4,5-bis(hydroxymethyl)-2-methylpyridin-3-ol, a form of vitamin B6.
Catalysis of a reaction in which S-adenosyl-L-methionine (SAM) undergoes reductive cleavage to serve as a source of the 5'-deoxyadenosyl radical.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-aminoimidazole ribonucleotide + S-adenosylmethionine -eq- 4-amino-5-hydroxymethyl-2-methylpyrimidine phosphate + 5'deoxyadenosine.
Combining with ferritin, and delivering ferritin into the cell via endocytosis.

A protein complex that binds iron and acts as a major iron storage system. Intracellular and extracellular ferritin complexes have different ratios of two types of ferritin monomer, the L (light) chain and H (heavy) chain.
A ferritin complex located in the extracellular region. Extracellular ferritin complexes contain L (light) chains but few or no H (heavy) chains.
Catalysis of the release of N-acylethanolamine from N-acyl-phosphatidylethanolamine (NAPE) to generate N-acylethanolamine (NAE).

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidic acid, any of a class of glycerol phosphate in which both the remaining hydroxyl groups of the glycerol moiety are esterified with fatty acids.

A protein complex that contains the protein kinase ATR and ATR-interacting protein (ATRIP) and binds single-stranded DNA -  ssDNA binding affinity is increased in the presence of replication protein A.

A protein complex that contains eight subunits in common with the SWI|SNF complex, plus the ATPase BRG1 (SMARCA4) and the histone methyltransferase CARM1 -  the complex is involved in regulating nuclear receptor-dependent transcription.
A nucleotide-excision repair complex formed by the association of the heterodimeric endonuclease XPF|ERCC4-ERCC1 (Rad1p and Rad10p in S. cerevisiae) with the RAD52 protein.

A protein complex formed by the association of RGS6, a negative regulator of heterotrimeric G protein signaling, with the DMAP1-Dnmt1 transcriptional repressor complex -  in the complex, RGS6 inhibits the transcriptional repressor activity of DMAP1.
A cell cycle arrest process that results in arrest during G1 phase, whereupon the cell enters a specialized resting state known as G0 or quiescence.

label.value: G1 to G0 transition involved in cell differentiation

definition.value: A cell cycle arrest process that results in arrest during G1 phase, whereupon the cell enters G0 phase, in the context of cell differentiation.

label.value: regulation of G0 to G1 transition

definition.value: A cell cycle process that modulates the rate or extent of the transition from the G0 quiescent state to the G1 phase.

label.value: negative regulation of G0 to G1 transition

definition.value: A cell cycle process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate or extent of the transition from the G0 quiescent state to the G1 phase.

label.value: positive regulation of G0 to G1 transition

definition.value: A cell cycle process that activates or increases the rate or extent of the transition from the G0 quiescent state to the G1 phase.

label.value: Golgi to plasma membrane transport vesicle

definition.value: A transport vesicle that mediates transport from the Golgi to the plasma membrane, and fuses with the plasma membrane to release various cargo molecules, such as proteins or hormones, by exocytosis.

label.value: inward rectifier potassium channel inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents, or reduces the activity of an inwardly rectifying potassium channel.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with thyroxine (T4) or triiodothyronine (T3), tyrosine-based hormones produced by the thyroid gland.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a lipoprotein particle receptor.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a very-low-density lipoprotein receptor.
Catalysis of the reduction of an aliphatic ring to yield an aromatic ring.
A protein complex that contains the cell-surface protein CD20 and the Src family tyrosine kinases Lck and Fyn.
A protein complex that contains the cell-surface protein CD20 and the Src family tyrosine kinases Lck, Lyn and Fyn.
A protein complex that consists of an alpha6-beta4 integrin complex bound to the adaptor proteins Shc and Grb2.
A protein complex that consists of an alpha6-beta4 integrin complex bound to laminin 5.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with aspartate, the alpha-amino-acid anion of 2-aminobutanedioic acid that has formula C4H5NO4.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a flap structure in DNA. A DNA flap structure is one in which a single-stranded length of DNA or RNA protrudes from a double-stranded DNA molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a 3'-flap structure in DNA. A DNA flap structure is one in which a single-stranded 3'-end of DNA or RNA protrudes from a double-stranded DNA molecule.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a 5'-flap structure in DNA. A DNA flap structure is one in which a single-stranded 5'-end of DNA or RNA protrudes from a double-stranded DNA molecule. 5'-flap structures can be formed during DNA repair or lagging strand synthesis -  in the latter case RNA flaps form from lagging strand RNA primers.

The multiplication or reproduction of fat cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A fat cell is an animal connective tissue cell specialized for the synthesis and storage of fat.

The multiplication or reproduction of brown fat cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A brown fat cell is a fat cell found the thermogenic form of adipose tissue found in newborns of many species.
The multiplication or reproduction of white fat cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label.value: regulation of brown fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of brown fat cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of brown fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of brown fat cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of brown fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of brown fat cell proliferation.

label.value: regulation of white fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of white fat cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of white fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of white fat cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of white fat cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of white fat cell proliferation.
